<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls strcmp(upg_header, WS_UPGRADE_VALUE) without guaranteeing that upg_header points to a NUL-terminated buffer. upg_header is taken from MHD_lookup_connection_value which returns pos->value from the connection headers; if the underlying header storage uses an explicit value_size and does not ensure a terminating '\0' (or if a malformed/truncated header results in no terminator), strcmp will read past the bounds of the value buffer while searching for a terminator, causing an out-of-bounds access. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. A safe approach would be to use a length-aware comparison (e.g. check the known value_size equals strlen(WS_UPGRADE_VALUE) and use memcmp/strncmp or MHD_str_equal_caseless_bin_n_) to avoid reads beyond the object bounds.
</scenario>
